After searching for one day I choose and configured collectd, version 5.12 to monitor my system usage across the time, including the usage of CPU, memory, root disk, and network interface. Gaved it up, write my own project instead, which fits my need better: luce-python Reference: https://wiki.archlinux.org/title/Collectd It is generally simple, just need to enable the plugins: cpu, memory, disk, df, and interface, then configuring for a while, everything is done then. It does not consume much resources and easy to use. Here are the four scripts I used to generate figures using rddtool. 12345678910111213141516171819202122232425262728293031323334353637383940414243#!/bin/bash# Usage: ./cpu_usage.sh &lt;start&gt; &lt;end&gt;# Example: ./cpu_usage.sh -86400 now (for the last 24 hours)START=$&#123;1:--86400&#125; # Default to the last 24 hours if not providedEND=$&#123;2:-now&#125; # Default to &#x27;now&#x27; if not providedrrdtool graph avg-cpu-usage.png \--start $START --end $END \--width 800 --height 400 \--title &quot;Average CPU Usage&quot; \--vertical-label &quot;CPU Usage (%)&quot; \--y-grid 10:1 \--font TITLE:14: \--font AXIS:10: \--font LEGEND:12: \--font UNIT:10: \DEF:cpu0=/var/lib/collectd/rrd/archlinux/cpu-0/percent-idle.rrd:value:AVERAGE \DEF:cpu1=/var/lib/collectd/rrd/archlinux/cpu-1/percent-idle.rrd:value:AVERAGE \DEF:cpu2=/var/lib/collectd/rrd/archlinux/cpu-2/percent-idle.rrd:value:AVERAGE \DEF:cpu3=/var/lib/collectd/rrd/archlinux/cpu-3/percent-idle.rrd:value:AVERAGE \DEF:cpu4=/var/lib/collectd/rrd/archlinux/cpu-4/percent-idle.rrd:value:AVERAGE \DEF:cpu5=/var/lib/collectd/rrd/archlinux/cpu-5/percent-idle.rrd:value:AVERAGE \DEF:cpu6=/var/lib/collectd/rrd/archlinux/cpu-6/percent-idle.rrd:value:AVERAGE \DEF:cpu7=/var/lib/collectd/rrd/archlinux/cpu-7/percent-idle.rrd:value:AVERAGE \DEF:cpu8=/var/lib/collectd/rrd/archlinux/cpu-8/percent-idle.rrd:value:AVERAGE \DEF:cpu9=/var/lib/collectd/rrd/archlinux/cpu-9/percent-idle.rrd:value:AVERAGE \DEF:cpu10=/var/lib/collectd/rrd/archlinux/cpu-10/percent-idle.rrd:value:AVERAGE \DEF:cpu11=/var/lib/collectd/rrd/archlinux/cpu-11/percent-idle.rrd:value:AVERAGE \DEF:cpu12=/var/lib/collectd/rrd/archlinux/cpu-12/percent-idle.rrd:value:AVERAGE \DEF:cpu13=/var/lib/collectd/rrd/archlinux/cpu-13/percent-idle.rrd:value:AVERAGE \DEF:cpu14=/var/lib/collectd/rrd/archlinux/cpu-14/percent-idle.rrd:value:AVERAGE \DEF:cpu15=/var/lib/collectd/rrd/archlinux/cpu-15/percent-idle.rrd:value:AVERAGE \CDEF:avg_cpu=cpu0,cpu1,+,cpu2,+,cpu3,+,cpu4,+,cpu5,+,cpu6,+,cpu7,+,cpu8,+,cpu9,+,cpu10,+,cpu11,+,cpu12,+,cpu13,+,cpu14,+,cpu15,+,16,/ \CDEF:cpu_usage=100,avg_cpu,- \CDEF:smoothed_cpu=cpu_usage,180,TREND \LINE2:smoothed_cpu#00FF00:&quot;Smoothed CPU Usage (%)&quot; \HRULE:80#FF0000:&quot;High CPU Usage (80%)&quot; \HRULE:90#FF6600:&quot;Critical CPU Usage (90%)&quot;echo &quot;CPU usage graph generated: avg-cpu-usage.png&quot; 12345678910111213141516171819202122232425262728#!/bin/bash# Usage: ./memory_usage.sh &lt;start&gt; &lt;end&gt;# Example: ./memory_usage.sh -1d now (for the last day)START=$&#123;1:-&quot;-1d&quot;&#125; # Default to last 24 hoursEND=$&#123;2:-&quot;now&quot;&#125; # Default to &#x27;now&#x27;rrdtool graph memory-usage.png \--start $START --end $END \--width 800 --height 400 \--title &quot;Memory Usage&quot; \--vertical-label &quot;Memory (GB)&quot; \--font TITLE:14: \--font AXIS:10: \--font LEGEND:12: \--font UNIT:10: \DEF:used=/var/lib/collectd/rrd/archlinux/memory/memory-used.rrd:value:AVERAGE \DEF:free=/var/lib/collectd/rrd/archlinux/memory/memory-free.rrd:value:AVERAGE \DEF:cached=/var/lib/collectd/rrd/archlinux/memory/memory-cached.rrd:value:AVERAGE \CDEF:used_gb=used,1073741824,/ \CDEF:free_gb=free,1073741824,/ \CDEF:cached_gb=cached,1073741824,/ \LINE2:used_gb#FF0000:&quot;Used Memory&quot; \LINE1:free_gb#00FF00:&quot;Free Memory&quot; \LINE1:cached_gb#0000FF:&quot;Cached Memory&quot;echo &quot;Memory usage graph generated: memory-usage.png&quot; 123456789101112131415161718192021222324252627#!/bin/bash# Usage: ./network_usage.sh &lt;start&gt; &lt;end&gt;# Example: ./network_usage.sh -1d now (for the last day)START=$&#123;1:-&quot;-1d&quot;&#125; # Default to last 24 hoursEND=$&#123;2:-&quot;now&quot;&#125; # Default to &#x27;now&#x27;rrdtool graph network-usage.png \--start $START --end $END \--width 800 --height 400 \--title &quot;Network Usage (wlan0)&quot; \--vertical-label &quot;Network (Bytes)&quot; \--font TITLE:14: \--font AXIS:10: \--font LEGEND:12: \--font UNIT:10: \DEF:rx=/var/lib/collectd/rrd/archlinux/interface-wlan0/if_octets.rrd:rx:AVERAGE \DEF:tx=/var/lib/collectd/rrd/archlinux/interface-wlan0/if_octets.rrd:tx:AVERAGE \LINE2:rx#00FF00:&quot;Received (Bytes)&quot; \LINE2:tx#0000FF:&quot;Transmitted (Bytes)&quot; \COMMENT:&quot;
&quot; \GPRINT:rx:AVERAGE:&quot;Avg Received\: %6.2lf Bytes&quot; \GPRINT:tx:AVERAGE:&quot;Avg Transmitted\: %6.2lf Bytes&quot; \COMMENT:&quot;
&quot;echo &quot;network usage graph generated: network-usage.png&quot; 123456789101112131415161718192021222324252627282930313233#!/bin/bash# Usage: ./disk_usage.sh &lt;start&gt; &lt;end&gt;# Example: ./disk_usage.sh -1d now (for the last day)START=$&#123;1:-&quot;-1d&quot;&#125; # Default to last 24 hoursEND=$&#123;2:-&quot;now&quot;&#125; # Default to &#x27;now&#x27;rrdtool graph disk-usage.png \--start $START --end $END \--width 800 --height 400 \--title &quot;Disk Usage (nvme0n1p2)&quot; \--vertical-label &quot;Disk Usage (GB)&quot; \--font TITLE:14: \--font AXIS:10: \--font LEGEND:12: \--font UNIT:10: \DEF:read=/var/lib/collectd/rrd/archlinux/disk-nvme0n1p2/disk_octets.rrd:read:AVERAGE \DEF:write=/var/lib/collectd/rrd/archlinux/disk-nvme0n1p2/disk_octets.rrd:write:AVERAGE \DEF:used_space=/var/lib/collectd/rrd/archlinux/df-root/df_complex-used.rrd:value:AVERAGE \CDEF:used_space_gb=used_space,1073741824,/ \CDEF:read_gb=read,1073741824,/ \CDEF:write_gb=write,1073741824,/ \LINE2:read_gb#FF0000:&quot;Read (GB)&quot; \LINE2:write_gb#0000FF:&quot;Write (GB)&quot; \LINE2:used_space_gb#FF8000:&quot;Used Disk Space (GB)&quot; \COMMENT:&quot;
&quot; \GPRINT:read_gb:AVERAGE:&quot;Avg Read\: %6.2lf GB&quot; \GPRINT:write_gb:AVERAGE:&quot;Avg Write\: %6.2lf GB&quot; \GPRINT:used_space_gb:LAST:&quot;Used Disk Space\: %6.2lf GB&quot; \COMMENT:&quot;
&quot;echo &quot;Disk usage graph generated: disk-usage.png&quot; Time formatRRDTool accepts several formats for specifying the start and end times when generating graphs. Here are some common formats: Common start and end Time Formats Absolute time: Format: YYYYMMDDHHMMSS Example: 20240912120000 (for September 12, 2024, at 12:00:00) Relative time: Use relative values such as now or time offsets. Examples: -1h: One hour ago -1d: One day ago -1w: One week ago -1m: One month ago -1y: One year ago -1: One second ago now: Current time Human-readable time: Format: start, end, or combinations of human-readable keywords. Examples: &quot;12:00&quot; &quot;yesterday&quot; &quot;midnight&quot; &quot;noon&quot;
